place.name: STANFORD
place.gazetteerText: STANFORD, a parish, with a village, in Swaffham district, Norfolk; 7 miles NE of Brandon r. station. Post town, Brandon. Acres, 2,608. Real property, £1,166. Pop., 200. Houses, 31. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £80. Patron, the Bishop of N. The church was recently rebuilt. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
